[32m+[m[32m## T-026 (2026-05-23)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Reason:** PRD segment container format is incompatible with standard HLS[m
[32m+[m[32m  players[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Details:** T-024 emits Ogg/Opus segments (`.opus` files) and T-025 stores[m
[32m+[m[32m  them under `cypherclaw/live/{date}/seg-{seq}.opus`. T-026 adds the[m
[32m+[m[32m  `GET /api/cypherclaw/live.m3u8` playlist and `GET /api/cypherclaw/segment/...`[m
[32m+[m[32m  retrieval endpoints exactly per the PRD, and the emitted playlist is a[m
[32m+[m[32m  valid HLS manifest (`#EXTM3U`, `#EXT-X-VERSION:3`, `#EXT-X-TARGETDURATION`,[m
[32m+[m[32m  `#EXT-X-MEDIA-SEQUENCE`, ordered `#EXTINF` + URI pairs). However, the[m
[32m+[m[32m  acceptance criterion ("`hls.js` validator or `ffplay` successfully plays the[m
[32m+[m[32m  live stream") cannot be satisfied with raw Ogg/Opus segments: ffmpeg's HLS[m
[32m+[m[32m  demuxer rejects `.opus` segment extensions (`URL ... is not in[m
[32m+[m[32m  allowed_segment_extensions`) even with `-allowed_extensions ALL`, because[m
[32m+[m[32m  raw Ogg is not a supported HLS segment container. hls.js has the same[m
[32m+[m[32m  limitation. Standard HLS requires CMAF/fMP4 (`.m4s`) or MPEG-TS (`.ts`); both[m
[32m+[m[32m  can carry Opus.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Recommendation:** Follow-on task on T-024 to re-package each 6-second[m
[32m+[m[32m  segment as fragmented MP4 (CMAF, `.m4s`) carrying the existing Opus stream,[m
[32m+[m[32m  and adjust T-025's R2 key suffix accordingly. The T-026 playlist endpoint[m
[32m+[m[32m  here is forward-compatible: it derives the segment URI from the R2 key and[m
[32m+[m[32m  the `#EXTINF` duration from R2 custom metadata, so once the suffix and[m
[32m+[m[32m  container change in T-024, the playlist will start serving HLS-playable[m
[32m+[m[32m  segments with no Worker change required.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Scope decision:** Shipping the playlist + retrieval endpoints now per[m
[32m+[m[32m  CC-022, because the segment container format is a structural T-024 concern[m
[32m+[m[32m  and rewriting the encoder is out of T-026's scope. Worker tests[m
[32m+[m[32m  (`npm test`, `npx tsc --noEmit`) and PromptClaw regression anchors stay[m
[32m+[m[32m  green.[m
